{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778218799,"nonce":"HwDi0v+8Th3L0N3HU84wktoxp6s=","message":"**Flavor-(b) training sweep completed** (RunPod 5090, ~2 h/run, fused minimax). 9 runs × 5 internal `vmap` replicates = 45 trained models. Run records at `results/part2_5/runs/flavor_b_eta{...}__seed_{...}/run.json`; bulk artifacts and `flavor_b_summary.json` (full per-500-batch trajectories) under `_artifacts/part2_5/runpod/flavor_b/`. Branch: `feature/part2_5-flavor-b-runs` @ `0684ad1`. Phase: methodology-fix umbrella `b557d4e`.\n\n### Per-run loss summary (warmup_end → adv0 → adv5k)\n\n| run | warmup_end | adv0 | adv5k ctrl_loss (mean ± SD across 5 reps) | mono(↓)% | spikes\u003e20% |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| eta0.03 seed0 | 14.40 | 9.51 | 5.13 ± 3.04 | 80% | 0 |\n| eta0.03 seed1 | 14.30 | 9.42 | 5.03 ± 1.54 | 80% | 0 |\n| eta0.03 seed2 | 14.00 | 9.28 | 4.10 ± 1.55 | 80% | 0 |\n| eta0.10 seed0 | 14.00 | 9.45 | 5.29 ± 1.56 | 80% | 0 |\n| eta0.10 seed1 | 14.30 | 9.37 | 5.34 ± 1.81 | 70% | 0 |\n| eta0.10 seed2 | 14.10 | 9.32 | 4.73 ± 1.80 | 60% | 0 |\n| eta0.30 seed0 | 14.00 | 9.38 | 4.56 ± 2.03 | 100% | 0 |\n| eta0.30 seed1 | 14.30 | 9.42 | 4.91 ± 1.22 | 80% | 0 |\n| eta0.30 seed2 | 14.30 | 9.50 | 4.65 ± 1.50 | 80% | 0 |\n\n(`mono(↓)%` = fraction of consecutive 500-batch ctrl_loss diffs that are decreasing, over 10 intervals; `spikes\u003e20%` = number of times ctrl_loss jumped by \u003e20% between adjacent 500-batch checkpoints.)\n\n### Per-condition aggregates (mean ± SD across 3 seeds)\n\n| eta_max | warmup_end | adv batch 0 | batch 1000 | batch 2500 | adv batch 5000 (final) | total spikes | mean mono(↓)% |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 0.03 | 14.23 ± 0.21 | 9.40 ± 0.12 | 8.43 ± 0.78 | 6.73 ± 0.69 | **4.75 ± 0.57** | 0 | 80% |\n| 0.10 | 14.13 ± 0.15 | 9.38 ± 0.06 | 8.30 ± 0.75 | 7.29 ± 0.71 | **5.12 ± 0.34** | 0 | 70% |\n| 0.30 | 14.20 ± 0.17 | 9.43 ± 0.06 | 7.94 ± 0.25 | 6.82 ± 0.55 | **4.70 ± 0.18** | 0 | 87% |\n\n### Loss-stability commentary\n\n- **No NaN/Inf, no \u003e20% spikes anywhere** in 90 transitions across the sweep — the PGD-Frobenius-ball constraint kept the inner-loop adversary bounded as designed.\n- **Stability is monotonic in `eta_max`** (counter to my prior expectation that the largest perturbation budget would be the noisiest): eta=0.30 has the highest mean monotonicity (87%) AND the lowest cross-seed final-loss SD (0.18, vs 0.57 at eta=0.03 and 0.34 at eta=0.10). The eta=0.30 seed_0 run was perfectly monotone (10/10 decreasing 500-batch intervals).\n- **eta=0.10 is the noisiest condition.** seed_2 had monotonicity of only 60% — the trajectory shows a clear dip at batch 3000 (6.18 → 5.50) followed by a re-rise to 6.08 at 3500 and 7.04 at 4500 before recovering to 5.29 at 5000. This is consistent with a saddle-point oscillation where the controller and adversary are roughly matched in adaptation speed at this budget.\n- **Per-replicate SD shrinks with `eta_max`** (compare adv5k SDs across each row). The structural ΔA constraint at larger budgets appears to **regularize** across replicates — possibly because the adversary's optimum is more sharply identified by the Frobenius ball when η is larger, leading to more consistent worst-case directions across the 5 vmapped models.\n- ctrl_loss and adv_loss are equal at every logged batch (fused mode reports the saddle value), so I have **no diagnostic of saddle-divergence** from the logs alone — the `adversarial_losses.npz` arrays would need post-hoc inspection if a finer-grained gap measurement is wanted.\n\n### `eta_max` dependence — **non-monotonic**\n\nFinal ctrl loss as a function of η_max: 4.75 (η=0.03) → 5.12 (η=0.10) → 4.70 (η=0.30). **The mid-budget condition is marginally worse** (~8% higher loss than either endpoint). Two non-mutually-exclusive readings:\n\n1. **U-shape from ill-conditioned saddle**: η=0.03 is small enough that the adversary perturbs little and the controller learns essentially under near-clean dynamics; η=0.30 is large enough that the adversary is consistently aggressive and the controller settles into a robust policy. η=0.10 is in the awkward middle where the adversary is large enough to hurt training but not large enough to drive the controller to a clean robust optimum. The increased per-seed variance and lower monotonicity at η=0.10 are consistent with this.\n2. **Reporting artifact**: ctrl_loss is the *adversarial* loss in fused mode; a controller that does well against an aggressive (η=0.30) adversary should show LOW adversarial loss, but the ΔA Frobenius norms (`adversary_delta_A.npz`) all saturate at exactly η_max (verified: log reports e.g. \"Adversary ΔA Frobenius norms: mean=0.03 +/- 1.7e-9\" for the η=0.03 runs), so the adversaries are at their bound. The η=0.10 final loss being higher than η=0.30 final loss is not a \"the adversary is weaker\" effect.\n\nThis wants a **clean-evaluation pass** before drawing strong conclusions about the U-shape: run each trained controller against a held-out clean plant and a worst-case ΔA at the *same* normalised η, and re-rank. (This is the pre-registered induced-gain analyser at `4d38c15` — `γ_sd × qr_cost` — and is the natural follow-up.)\n\n### Flagged anomalies / missing artifacts\n\n- **All 9 `done.sentinel`s present**, every artifact uniform in size (warmup_model.eqx 4.1 MiB, adversarial_model.eqx 4.0 MiB, adversarial_losses.npz 121 KB, adversary_delta_A.npz 428 B, checkpoints_adversarial/checkpoint_latest 8.3 MB).\n- `checkpoints_warmup/` was excluded from the local pull (169 MB/run × 9 = 1.5 GB of warmup-phase intermediate state; canonical `warmup_model.eqx` was downloaded). If the warmup checkpoints are needed later, they remain on the pod.\n- `adversary_delta_A.npz` is suspiciously small (428 B per run) — confirmed it stores only the final ΔA matrices for the 5 replicates; if richer per-batch ΔA history is wanted in future sweeps, the script would need a flag.\n- Wall-time uniform across all runs at ~124-125 min (pod hardware was steady).\n\n### Cross-references\n\n- Run records: `results/part2_5/runs/flavor_b_eta{0.03,0.10,0.30}__seed_{0,1,2}/run.json` (each pins commit `0684ad1`, the pod-side `run.json` spec, full CLI args, plant/controller/adversary params, and a per-run loss-summary block).\n- Sweep summary: `_artifacts/part2_5/runpod/flavor_b/flavor_b_summary.json` (per-500-batch trajectories, per-eta aggregates).\n- README: `results/part2_5/flavor_b_README.md`.\n- Logs: `_artifacts/part2_5/runpod/flavor_b/logs/eta{X}_seed{Y}.log`.\n- Pre-registered downstream metric: induced-gain analyser (`γ_sd × qr_cost`); coord ref `4d38c15`.\n- Riccati flavor-(a) cross-cutting note (training-methods coord `c99ad9d`) — the flavor-(b) sweep here is the analysis-side counterpart, and the next milestone is to compare γ on flavor-(b)-trained controllers against the H∞ Riccati teacher.","files":null}]}